    &lt;div class="product-body"&gt;&lt;h3 style="color: Red; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: Yellow;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Guide to Constructing Hydrophones&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
and Hydrophone Arrays for Monitoring&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Marine Mammal Vocalizations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: Yellow;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instant Download! Only 4.99&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Blue; text-align: center;"&gt;See Picture Below for completed Hydrophone!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0); text-align: center;"&gt;Build A Hydrophone &amp; Listen to Underwater Mammals!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Blue; text-align: center;"&gt;With your home made hydrophone you can listen to whales and dolphins and more!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Red; text-align: center;"&gt;Here is a sample of the range of this device!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Blue; text-align: justify;"&gt;Marine mammal vocalizations or linear hydrophone arrays in which several hydrophones are molded&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
onto a single cable for localizing a sound source. This guide is intended for anyone with an interest in&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
building hydrophones, and no special expertise is required. The hydrophones described below are&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
based on an EC65 cylindrical hydrophone element and a&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
lownoise&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
preamplifier. This combination has proven to be reliable, gives a very clean sound (up to&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
approximately 40 kHz), and is excellent for receiving sounds from sperm whales, humpback whales,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
and several dolphin species.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The preamp incorporates a high-pass filter that reduces flow noise that occurs when towing the&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
hydrophones. A very small modification can be made to remove this filter and extend the usable&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
frequency response down to a few Hz. Note that even with this modification, the hydrophones are not&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
linear in frequency response. An example calibration is provided. Some sound analysis software can&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
compensate for a known frequency response to restore linearity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The building process described here consists of many steps, none of which are difficult. Some steps,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
however, have little margin for error. Be sure youve had your coffee first. But not too much!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Red; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: Yellow;"&gt;Comes with complete parts list! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Red; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: Yellow;"&gt;Comes with color pictures and step by step instructions! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="color: Red; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: Yellow;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14px;"&gt;Hydrophone Plans Instant Dowload Only 4.99 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
